<p>I'm trying to learn how to use named groups properly and for some reason i dont know how to use <strong>preg_replace</strong> with named groups.</p>  <p>For example without named groups:</p>  <pre><code>$str = som,ething; $regex = '/(\w*)[^\w](\w*)/'; $replace = '${1}${2}';  preg_replace($regex, $replace, $str); </code></pre>  <p>Output:<br></p>  <blockquote>   <p>something</p> </blockquote>  <p>But if I try to use named groups:</p>  <pre><code>$str = som,ething; $regex = '/(?&lt;foo&gt;\w*)[^\w](?&lt;bar&gt;\w*)/'; $replace = '${foo}${bar}';  preg_replace($regex, $replace, $str); </code></pre>  <p>The output will be:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>${foo}${bar}</p> </blockquote>